    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-04-05T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-04-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="199"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d199">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Burnley</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Seward</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-04-05">
                            <hi rend="italic">April</hi> 5, 1865.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Since I had the honor of addressing you on the
                    27th of February, respecting that portion of the cotton captured at Savannah
                    which is said to be the property of British subjects, her Majesty’s government
                    have had under their consideration the further correspondence which has been
                    forwarded to them from time to time, and now instruct me to express to you their
                    confident hope that no obstacle will be interposed to prevent her Majesty’s
                    subjects from establishing their just claims to their own property.</p>
                <p>I have the honor to be, with the highest consideration, sir, your most obedient,
                    humble servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>J. HUME BURNLEY.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">William H. Seward,</hi>
                        <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c</hi>.</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
